I"Ó<h1 id="01-knowledge">01 Knowledge</h1>

<p>Representing information and drawing inferences from it.</p>

<h2 id="basic-terminology">Basic terminology</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>knowledge-based agents</p>

    <p>agents that reason by operating on internal representations of knowledge</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>sentence</p>

    <p>an assertion about the world in a knowledge representation language</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>model</p>

    <p>assignment of a truth value to every propositional symbol (a ‚Äúpossible world‚Äù)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>knowledge base</p>

    <p>a set of sentences known by a knowledge-based agent</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>inference</p>

    <p>the process of deriving new sentences from old ones</p>
  </li>
</ul>

